`crates/ctx-core` is a single-crate wrapper: its entire content is `src/`, whose rollup already documents the crate's purpose and cross-crate contracts in full. There is no crate-level glue, feature configuration, or additional module structure to add beyond what's in `src/rollup.ctx` — `Cargo.toml` just declares the crate and its (minimal/no) dependencies.

Depending on `ctx-core` buys exactly what `src/rollup.ctx` describes: the canonical denylist, hash-sidecar schema, and STATUS.md table codec, all pure and dependency-free. Nothing at this level changes that contract.

No intent.md exists for this directory to check against.